{
  "message": "fuzz(fj-conformance): add partial_eval_fuzzer for fj-interpreters\n\nNew fuzz target for partial evaluation (Jaxpr splitting):\n- Generates Jaxprs from ProgramSpec and random known/unknown masks\n- Verifies structural invariants on PartialEvalResult:\n  - out_unknowns length matches original outputs\n  - unknown jaxpr inputs = residuals + original unknown inputs\n  - all-known inputs produce all-known outputs with no residuals\n  - all-unknown inputs produce empty known jaxpr\n\n16 corpus seeds covering:\n- All-known paths (add2, square, sinx, cosx, etc.)\n- All-unknown paths\n- Mixed known/unknown patterns (first vs second input)\n- Various ProgramSpecs (Add2, Square, Dot3, etc.)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
